---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import CTABanner from '../components/CTABanner.astro';
---

<Layout title="SafetyStatus — Equipment Management International" description="SafetyStatus replaces generic paper checklists with structured, mobility-based safety audits and inspections for mining sites. Available on iPad.">
  <Nav />
  <main id="top" class="pt-20">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <PageHero
      title="SafetyStatus"
      subtitle="Tech-based solutions for structured and practical safety audits and inspections"
    >
      <div class="mt-4">
        <img src="/images/products/safety-status-logo.png" alt="SafetyStatus logo" class="h-24 sm:h-32 rounded-lg" />
      </div>
    </PageHero>

    <!-- Opening Statement -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="space-y-4 prose-body">
          <p>
            SafetyStatus allows you to remove generic paper-based work area safety checklists that slow down your operation. And with a focus on safe and efficient processes, the data is easier to collect, analyse, and make decisions on.
          </p>
          <p>
            Mining companies have been doing things the same way for years, without anyone questioning these typical methods. But there are many common issues with the usual site inspection checklist methods.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Issues -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-200">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-8">
          Do Any of These Sound Familiar?
        </h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          {[
            'Limited direction or guidelines due to lack of available content',
            'Inexperienced workers assigned to roles with no prior preparation',
            'Lack of awareness of potential risks involved',
            'Management unaware of where time is actually being spent',
            'Paper-based field audits and inspections with one-size-fits-all forms',
            'Time wasted performing and reporting due to limited flow or structure',
            'Rehandling of documents and delays in vital communication',
          ].map((issue) => (
            <div class="card bg-base-100">
              <div class="card-body flex-row items-start gap-3 p-5">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-error flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.833-1.964-.833-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z"/></svg>
                <p>{issue}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="text-center text-primary font-semibold mt-8 text-lg">
          What if there was a better and safer way to carry out safety audits and inspections to solve all these issues? SafetyStatus is that solution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product Features -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading mb-8">How SafetyStatus Works</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 prose-body">
          <p>
            Finally, a mobility-based software that prepares complex safety audit processes and procedures into easy-to-read and simple-to-follow structured tasks that flow with your work area.
          </p>
          <p>
            SafetyStatus electronically maps out for an inspector what needs to be checked, when, and how. It also details any potential risks involved and what's required in the way of tools and permits, so nothing is missed. Images, videos and PDFs can also be used to support each task.
          </p>
          <p>
            When an inspector spots an issue, it can be recorded electronically, risk-rated for future rectification priority, and images of the finding can be captured. This means any previously reported or outstanding findings can easily be viewed, edited, and the status of the work area updated.
          </p>
          <p>
            Plus, technical questions are used as prompts to determine the actual condition of the work area. Any values that fall outside the min/max range automatically trigger a reporting process for the issue.
          </p>
          <p class="font-semibold text-base-content">
            SafetyStatus enables auditors and inspectors to perform their tasks to the standard expected by your company — safely, efficiently, and with purpose and value.
          </p>
          <p class="text-primary font-semibold">
            Now available on iPad.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Products -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-200">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-12">
          Other Status Suite Products
        </h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h3 class="card-title">ComponentStatus</h3>
              <div class="badge badge-primary badge-outline">Component Rebuilds</div>
              <p class="mt-2">
                Share complex work instructions for any task-based process simply and electronically. Each step clearly defines what the task is and how to do it.
              </p>
              <div class="card-actions mt-4">
                <a href="/componentstatus" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Learn More</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h3 class="card-title">EquipmentStatus</h3>
              <div class="badge badge-primary badge-outline">Equipment Compliance</div>
              <p class="mt-2">
                Designed to support equipment condition compliance. Ideally suited for rental equipment return inspections and release compliance, or MDG15 equipment audits.
              </p>
              <div class="card-actions mt-4">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Request a Demo</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h3 class="card-title">EnviroStatus</h3>
              <div class="badge badge-primary badge-outline">Environmental Audits</div>
              <p class="mt-2">
                Collect in-field data to monitor environmental condition and compliance requirements in near real-time.
              </p>
              <div class="card-actions mt-4">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Request a Demo</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <CTABanner
      heading="Ready to Upgrade Your Safety Audits?"
      subtitle="Request a demo to see how SafetyStatus can transform your inspection processes."
      primaryLabel="Request a Demo"
      primaryHref="/contact"
      secondaryLabel="Take Action"
      secondaryHref="/take-action"
    />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
